# ListMyNest — Frontend Cursor Rules
# Always read README.md, PRD.md, TRD.md before starting any task.
# Reference them with @README.md @PRD.md @TRD.md in every new chat session.

## Project
You are building ListMyNest — a mobile-first real estate discovery PWA for Tier-3 Indian cities
(Bidar, Humnabad, Basavakalyan, Bhalki, Aurad, Karnataka).

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14.2.3 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- Zustand 4.5.2 (state management)
- TanStack React Query 5.32.0 (data fetching)
- next-pwa (PWA / service worker)
- PostHog for analytics (posthog-js 1.121.0)
- Google Maps JS API (Places + Geocoding)

## Folder Conventions
- app/           → Next.js App Router pages (SSR/SSG/CSR per page rules below)
- components/    → Reusable UI components, grouped by domain (property/, buyer/, seller/, etc.)
- store/         → Zustand stores only
- hooks/         → Custom React hooks only
- lib/api/       → All API call functions (never fetch inline in components)
- lib/utils/     → Pure utility functions
- types/         → TypeScript interfaces and enums

## Rendering Rules (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
- /property/[id]     → SSR always (SEO critical, use generateMetadata)
- /listings          → SSR (city/type filters need server-side rendering)
- / (homepage)       → SSG with revalidate: 300
- /saved             → CSR only (requires buyer token)
- /seller/**         → CSR (authenticated, no SEO needed)
- /agent/**          → CSR (authenticated, no SEO needed)
- /admin/**          → CSR (authenticated, no SEO needed)

## Security Rules (NEVER violate these)
1. NEVER render seller_phone or agent_phone anywhere in the frontend
2. buyer_token → ONLY sessionStorage, never localStorage or cookies
3. Before ANY contact action (Call Now / WhatsApp), POST /leads first — then complete the action
4. Only fetch agent WA number from /whatsapp/link/{propertyId} — never from property detail response
5. PostHog must use persistence: 'memory' (DPDP Act compliance — no localStorage tracking)
6. Session hash = SHA-256(userAgent + date + screenSize) — no PII ever

## Camera / Photo Rules
- Photo upload inputs must always have: accept="image/*" capture="environment"
- GPS EXIF extracted client-side via exifr for preview only; backend always re-validates

## State Management Rules
- buyerStore: { buyerToken, buyerId } — hydrate from sessionStorage on init
- sessionStore: { viewedPropertyIds, contactActionTaken, notifyMeShown } — sessionStorage only
- filterStore: { city, propertyType, priceMin, priceMax } — no persistence needed

## 4-Moment Contact Capture (Business Critical)
Implement in useContactCapture() hook:
1. WhatsApp tap → POST /leads (type=WHATSAPP) → fetch /whatsapp/link/{id} → open wa.me link
2. Schedule Visit → phone required on form (buyer_phone NOT NULL)
3. Post-Visit WA → triggered by backend on agent marking VISITED
4. Notify Me sheet → show when viewCount >= 3 AND !contactActionTaken AND !notifyMeShown

## Component Style Rules
- Mobile-first: design at 360px width first, then scale up
- Tailwind only — no inline styles except dynamic values (e.g. width percentages)
- Price always displayed as ₹X Lakh range, never exact amount
- Property cards NEVER show seller/agent contact info
- All API calls via lib/api/ functions, never raw fetch in components

## API Base URL
process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL (never hardcode)

## Testing
- Playwright for E2E: 5 critical flows must pass before any PR merge
  1. browse → WhatsApp click (lead logged before WA opens)
  2. browse → schedule visit
  3. save with OTP flow
  4. notify-me bottom sheet trigger
  5. saved tab display
